<bioghist encodinganalog="545">
<p>Holy Cross Church is a Catholic church which ministered to the Native American community of Cross Village, Michigan.</p>
</bioghist>



<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
<p>The records of the church date back to 1847 and include baptismal records, marriage, birth and death records, photographs, newspaper clippings and printed histories detailing activities of this Indian church. Most of the records are in Latin and Ottawa.</p>
</scopecontent>

